ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely I will. This is an intensive and engaging course on Horace from which everyone can take away a lot.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The Classics Departments' expertise in Roman satire is one of the reasons I came to study at Yale, and this was an extremely helpful course. We got a very in-depth overview of not only Horace's Satires, but also his Epistles. Discussion in class was very lively and encouraged me to sharpen my arguments further and further.
This course helped me to achieve much better understanding and knowledge on the supject. It also improved my latin reading skill a lot.
